	 <!--Title for Page-->
	<h1> Legal Image Sources </h1>
	<!--A descritpion of legal resources-->
	<p>Legal image sources are resources of images that can be found and used online while respecting copyright laws,
	   by focusing on images with license, permitting reuse, distribution, or those in the public domain.
	   There are numerous of different websites that you can used to find images that are legal to reuse.</p>
	   
	   <!-- List and description of websites that provide free and legally usable images-->
	   
	   <h2>Websites that are free and have Legally usable Images</h2>
	   <ul>
	      <li> <Strong>Unsplash:</strong> This is a website that provides over 6 million free images. You can 
           find high-resolution photos and illustrations from professional photographers and different other artists.
           You can apply for job oppourtunities and submit your own images to the site.  They hand pick all images 
           that are found on the website.</li>
		   
		   <li><strong>Pexels:</strong>Provides high quality and completely free stock photos licensed under the 
		   Pexels license.  They help millions of designers, writers, artists, programmers and other creators to get access 
		   to beautiful photos that they can use freely which empowers them to create amazing products, designs, stories, 
		   websites, apps, art and other work.  All photos are nicely tagged, searchable and also easy to discover through 
		   their discover pages.  They have hundreds of thousands free stock photos and every day new high resolution photos are added. 
		   All photos are hand-picked from photos uploaded by users or sourced from free image websites. </li>
		   
		   <li><strong>Pixabay:</strong> This website delivers free stock photos, illustrations, vector graphics, videos, 
		    music and sounds effects. Shared and enjoyed by one of the largest creator communities in the world.  Pixabay allows you 
           to upload your material, build a creative portfolio, be selected in Pixabay curations, get hired, receive donations and 
		   inspire millions. Pixabay allolws you to connect with other creators, receive feedback, ask or answer questions from the community.
           They offer events, workshops,contests, and more for users of this webpage.		   
           </li>
		   <li><strong>Flickr Commons:</strong> This is a general photo-sharing platform, its "Commons" section focuses on images that
		   are freely licensed, often under Creative Commons licenses, which allows for various levels of use, including commercial use, 
		   with attribution. </li>
		 
		    <li><strong>Creative Commons Search:</strong> This is a search engine that allows you to find images, videos, and other media that are licensed 
			under Creative Commons licenses. It grants permission for reuse, often with specific conditions like attribution or non-commercial use. 
			</li>
			
			<li><strong>Wikimedia Commons:</strong>A storehouse of open-licensed and public domain images, videos, and other media, often used on Wikipedia, 
			with images licensed under Creative Commons or in the public domain. </li>
			
			<li><strong>Public Domain Pictures</strong> This is a storehouse for free, high-quality public domain photos and images. </li>
			
		 </ul>
		 
		 </body>
		 
		 </html>
